<div class="d-flex justify-content-between align-items-center mb-4">
    <div>
        <div class="badge-soft mb-2">Food &amp; Cuisine</div>
        <h2 class="fw-bold mb-1">Flavours of Maharashtra</h2>
        <p class="text-muted mb-0">
            From street food favourites to homely festive dishes, Maharashtrian cuisine is diverse and deeply regional.
        </p>
    </div>
    <a href="index.jsp" class="btn btn-outline-secondary d-none d-md-inline-flex">Back to Home</a>
</div>

<div class="row g-4">
    <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-4">
        <div class="card section-card h-100">
            <img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/4611420/pexels-photo-4611420.jpeg"
                 class="card-img-top" alt="Vada Pav street food">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title">Vada Pav</h5>
                <p class="card-text text-muted">
                    Often called the “Indian burger”, Vada Pav is Mumbai’s most iconic street food – a spicy
                    potato fritter (vada) placed inside a pav (bread roll) with chutneys and fried chillies.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-4">
        <div class="card section-card h-100">
            <img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/1437268/pexels-photo-1437268.jpeg"
                 class="card-img-top" alt="Misal Pav served in bowl">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title">Misal Pav</h5>
                <p class="card-text text-muted">
                    A spicy curry of sprouted lentils topped with farsan (crunchy mixture), onions and coriander,
                    served with pav. Popular breakfast and brunch dish, especially in Pune and Kolhapur.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-4">
        <div class="card section-card h-100">
            <img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/7525186/pexels-photo-7525186.jpeg"
                 class="card-img-top" alt="Puran Poli sweet flatbread">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title">Puran Poli</h5>
                <p class="card-text text-muted">
                    A festive sweet flatbread stuffed with a mixture of cooked chana dal, jaggery and cardamom.
                    Traditionally prepared during festivals like Holi and Gudi Padwa.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="row g-4 mt-1 mt-md-3">
    <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-4">
        <div class="card section-card h-100">
            <img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/1438672/pexels-photo-1438672.jpeg"
                 class="card-img-top" alt="Fish curry and rice">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title">Coastal Seafood</h5>
                <p class="card-text text-muted">
                    Konkan and Malvani cuisine is known for flavourful fish curries, fried fish, solkadhi (kokum
                    and coconut drink) and a generous use of coconut, tamarind and spices.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-4">
        <div class="card section-card h-100">
            <img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/11170284/pexels-photo-11170284.jpeg"
                 class="card-img-top" alt="Traditional Indian thali">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title">Traditional Thali</h5>
                <p class="card-text text-muted">
                    A Maharashtrian thali typically includes bhakri or chapati, rice, lentils, sabzi,
                    koshimbir (salad), pickles and a sweet dish, offering a balanced and wholesome meal.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

